  "What is 'spectral graph theory'?": "",
  "A technique for drawing graphs visually": "",
  "Computing shortest paths using matrix multiplication": "",
  "Studying graphs using color frequencies": "",
  "Studying properties of graphs through eigenvalues and eigenvectors of associated matrices": "",
  "Spectral graph theory analyzes graph properties using the spectrum (eigenvalues) of matrices like the adjacency matrix or Laplacian. It connects linear algebra to combinatorial properties.": "",
  "What is the 'graph Laplacian' matrix?": "",
  "L = D - A, where D is the degree matrix and A is the adjacency matrix": "",
  "The transpose of the incidence matrix": "",
  "The inverse of the adjacency matrix": "",
  "The square of the adjacency matrix": "",
  "The Laplacian L = D - A is a positive semidefinite matrix where D is diagonal with vertex degrees. It encodes the graph structure and its eigenvalues reveal connectivity.": "",
  "What does 'spectral clustering' mean in machine learning?": "",
  "Partitioning data into clusters using eigenvectors of a similarity or Laplacian matrix": "",
  "Using k-means on the eigenvalues directly": "",
  "Clustering using color spectral analysis": "",
  "Clustering based on the spectrum of electromagnetic radiation": "",
